fields.label: Banner Type
fields.name: banner_type
fields.instructions: Select Custom to add the banner from this page. Select Universal to display the banner selected for all pages under "Client Settings" > Page banners.

fields.label: Banner Image
fields.name: banner_background_image
fields.instructions: For best quality, the image should be 1400px in width minimum (1200px is tolerated)

fields.label: Image Position
fields.name: image_position
fields.instructions: Select the vertical positioning of the image.

fields.label: Display Caption?
fields.name: display_caption
fields.instructions: Do you want to display a caption over the banner image?

fields.label: Caption Type
fields.name: caption_type
fields.instructions: Select the type of caption you would like to display

fields.label: Banner Caption
fields.name: banner_caption
fields.instructions: Use Heading 1 for main title and Heading 3 for subtitle.

fields.label: Profile Picture
fields.name: profile_picture
fields.instructions: Add a profile picture for blog authors.

fields.label: Logo Retina
fields.name: logo_retina
fields.instructions: Upload your organization's logo optimized at 2x the regular size for retina displays. This logo will also be used for regular display screens.

fields.label: Tracking ID
fields.name: tracking_id
fields.instructions: Add your Google analytics tracking ID (UA-000000)

fields.label: Container ID
fields.name: container_id
fields.instructions: Paste you container ID here

fields.label: Image Position
fields.name: error_page_banner_position
fields.instructions: Select the vertical positioning of the image.

fields.label: Image Position
fields.name: internal_page_banner_position
fields.instructions: Select the vertical positioning of the image.

fields.label: Image Position
fields.name: single_blog_post_banner_position
fields.instructions: Select the vertical positioning of the image.

fields.label: Image Position
fields.name: single_event_banner_position
fields.instructions: Select the vertical positioning of the image.

fields.label: Image Position
fields.name: search_page_banner_position
fields.instructions: Select the vertical positioning of the image.

fields.label: Image Position
fields.name: category_banner_position
fields.instructions: Select the vertical positioning of the image.

fields.label: Show Post Author
fields.name: show_post_author
fields.instructions: Check this box if you wish to display the post author name on single post page.

fields.label: Show Title
fields.name: show_engagement_title
fields.instructions: This will display the title set on top of this page and will render it on top of the engagement section.

sub_fields.message: This feature will allow you to add an image on the left and some text on the right. You can also choose to add a video which will open in a lightbox. The image will then have a color overlay and a play button over it. Use this option to feature a big event for instance.
sub_fields.label: About Engagement Feature

fields.label: Testimonial Author
fields.name: testimonial_author
fields.instructions: Enter name of testimonial author here. (optional)

fields.label: Image Type
fields.name: image_type
fields.instructions: Choose if the image should be a small image next to the testimonial a full width background image behind the text.

fields.message: Checking this box, will put the filter on the site, to display it in grayscale mode.
fields.label: Turn on prototype
fields.name: turn_on_prototype

fields.message: Check this box when any plugin updates are complete to avoid client installing unsupported plugins.
fields.label: Turn on plugin install
fields.name: turn_on_plugin_install

fields.message: Uncheck this box if you want to disable the theme updater (usually true for Custom WP builds)
fields.label: Update
fields.name: bb_theme_update
fields.instructions: IMPORTANT!: If the designer/developer unchecked this box, leave it unchecked. Checking it could wipe out important changes to the parent theme that could be wiped out by the theme updater.

fields.message: Check this box after building out your theme to make sure client cannot view the advanced custom fields page.
fields.label: Hide Advanced Custom Fields
fields.name: hide_acf
fields.instructions: If the website is live or the client has ben given access to Wordpress, this should be checked!

fields.label: Background Color
fields.name: admin_bg_clr
fields.instructions: Select the background color of the login page. (optional - can be used if logo is made of white text only for example)

fields.label: Custom fonts
fields.name: custom_fonts
fields.instructions: Paste custom font scripts (typekit, google font...) here.

fields.message: Check the box of the script you need for your theme
fields.label: Activate Scripts

fields.message: Uncheck the CPT you want to deactivate specifically for your theme.
fields.label: Unregister CPT
Activate Toolbar
fields.name: activate_toolbar
fields.instructions: By turning this option on, you will have the ability to choose what to include in the toolbar, that will be displaying under internal banners. (options include "breadcrumbs", "social share buttons" etc..)

fields.label: Show Social Sharing
fields.name: show_social_sharing
fields.instructions: Make sure to activate the Share This script under the "scripts" tab.

fields.label: Share Code
fields.name: share_code
fields.instructions: Paste the code from either ShareThis or AddThis to display the appropriate buttons. (default will be Twitter and Facebook Shares)

fields.label: Show Font Resizer
fields.name: show_font_resizer
fields.instructions: Make sure to activate the Font Resizer script under the "scripts" tab.

fields.label: Google API Key
fields.name: google_api_key
fields.instructions:
Need the client to have a google account and need access to that account to generate API key
This is for the ACF Google map field to work. Ai1ec has a field to add the API key. WP Google Map has an API key field as well.

fields.label: GT Code
fields.name: gt_code
fields.instructions: To add more languages, generate a new snippet of code following this link: https://translate.google.com/manager/website/add - then replace the entire code below.

fields.label: Menu Offcanvas
fields.name: menu_offcanvas
fields.instructions: Check this box if the menu should be offcanvas to the right.

fields.label: Events Category
fields.name: carousel_events_category
fields.instructions: Choose up to 1 category. If no category is selected then all events (up to 12) will be displayed from newest to oldest.

fields.label: Posts Category
fields.name: posts_category
fields.instructions: Choose up to 1 category. If no category is selected then all posts will be displayed from newest to oldest. (limit will be 12 posts for sliders and carousels)

sub_fields.label: Media Type
sub_fields.name: feature_media_type
sub_fields.instructions: Choose whether you want to display an image or embed a video (youtube or vimeo)

sub_fields.label: Feature Video
sub_fields.name: feature_video
sub_fields.instructions: Paste the direct link to your video (ie: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Qbb87xM_7iw)

sub_fields.label: Column Video
sub_fields.name: column_video
sub_fields.instructions: Paste Youtube URL here to load Video

sub_fields.label: Columns Content
sub_fields.name: columns_content
sub_fields.instructions: This module lets you create columns (minimum 2 and up to 4) with specific layout options.

sub_fields.label: Page Gallery
sub_fields.name: page_gallery
sub_fields.instructions: Choose Images that are at least 600px in width and 600px in height (minimum)

sub_fields.label: Select Latest Posts
sub_fields.name: select_latest_posts
sub_fields.instructions: Choose up to 1 category. If no category is selected then all posts will be displayed from newest to oldest.

sub_fields.label: Pagination
sub_fields.name: pagination
sub_fields.instructions: Enter the number of posts per page. (min 3, max 25)

sub_fields.label: Video URL
sub_fields.name: video_url
sub_fields.instructions: Paste the direct link to the video (ie:https://youtu.be/Qbb87xM_7iw)

fields.label: Link Text
fields.name: link_text
fields.instructions: This is the text that will appear on the call to action link or button.

fields.label: External URL
fields.name: external_url
fields.instructions: Enter full URL (http://blackbaud.com)

fields.label: Link Target
fields.name: link_target
fields.instructions: Open in a new tab?

fields.label: Add Icon
fields.name: add_icon
fields.instructions: Check this box to select an icon if the link is meant to be a button.

fields.label: Background Color
fields.name: background_color
fields.instructions: Brand Color 1 => purple - Brand Color 2 = orange - Brand Color 3 => light gray

fields.label: White Text
fields.name: white_text
fields.instructions: Check this box if the main text color should be set to white.

fields.label: Fix Background
fields.name: fix_background
fields.instructions: Check this box if the background image should be set to fixed.

fields.label: Background Position
fields.name: background_position
fields.instructions: Select the vertical positioning of the image. By default the image is centered but you can adjust this depending on the position of the subject(s) on the image.

sub_fields.message:
Adding this module will display the navigation based on the page location which will be generated from the Primary Navigation under 'Appearance' > 'Menus'.
This does not apply to posts or calendar events.
sub_fields.label: Side Navigation
Select Widgets Sidebar
sub_fields.name: select_widgets_sidebar
sub_fields.instructions: Create the new sidebar options under Client Settings > Sidebars. Then populate the sidebars under Appearance > Widgets. Finally, select the sidebar you want to use on this page.

fields.message: Choose your options for the homepage Slider
fields.label: Slider Options
Transition Speed
fields.name: transition_speed
fields.instructions: Choose the amount of time to delay between automatically cycling an item. (default 5000 = 5 seconds)

fields.message: Checking this box will allow the slider to pause when hovering over it.
fields.label: Pause on hover
fields.name: pause_on_hover

fields.message: Display navigation arrows? Those will show when hovering over the slider
fields.label: Show Arrows
fields.name: show_arrows

fields.message: Show slides indicators? This will display the dots at the bottom of the slider.
fields.label: Show Indicators
fields.name: show_indicators

sub_fields.label: Caption Position
sub_fields.name: caption_position
sub_fields.instructions: Select where you want the caption to display over the image. (this can vary according to subjects on images)

sub_fields.message: Adding this section will pull the 4 latest posts checked as "sticky" from the chosen category below.
sub_fields.label: Home News

fields.message: This is where you will have your page main content (text, images, links, videos, image galleries, iframe...)
fields.label: Page Content
Show Author Info
fields.name: show_author_info
fields.instructions: If you check this box, an author short bio can be displayed below the post as well as a link to the author's single page that has a bio and other posts by same author. Biography can be updated under "user" profile.

fields.label: Form Code
fields.name: form_code
fields.instructions: Paste here the code of the registration form if applicable. (ie: OLX...)

fields.message: Check this box if this event should be displayed on homepage.
fields.label: Home Featured
fields.name: home_featured
fields.instructions: This only applies for the Home Widget calendar with featured image.
